    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (69.58), who headlines our recommendations due to a favorable matchup against Gallen. Despite the wind inward, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from a massive 14% boost via dynamic platoon splits, making him our highest-projected asset. He is joined at the top of the tier by **Kazuma Okamoto** (63.91) and **Yordan Alvarez** (63.92); **Kazuma Okamoto** faces a generous 4.87 xERA from Woods Richardson, while **Yordan Alvarez** remains a lock given his elite 0.436 xwOBA, proving that his hitting prowess outweighs the negative L/L platoon adjustment. **Trea Turner** (63.69) also remains a critical start; his profile is buoyed by a \"slow delivery\" bonus from Eury P\u00e9rez, which is vital for maintaining our edge in the league\u2019s scarcest category, stolen bases.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Luke Raley**, who failed to crack the active roster with a score of 33.88. While his raw hitting ability is respected, the optimizer penalized him heavily for a brutal matchup against Cole Ragans (3.07 xERA) and an unfavorable L/L platoon situation, ultimately favoring the daily efficiency of players like **Carson Benge** (62.65), who benefits from a much softer matchup against Walbert Urena. We are also monitoring the status of **Gary Sanchez**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Trea Turner**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Junior Caminero**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Yordan Alvarez**, **Kyle Schwarber**, and **Carson Benge**, as all occupy lineup slots currently marked as \"Pending.\" While we have modeled these lineups based on historical data, any late-breaking roster shifts could force us to re-evaluate, particularly for **Caleb Durbin**, whose current 49.84 score remains sensitive to potential order changes. As a reminder, **Christian Yelich** remains on the IL, **Colt Keith** is currently benched, and **Zac Veen** is unavailable in the minors, leaving us limited flexibility should mid-day lineup changes occur.",
